# LAB 02 – Enterprise VLAN Design & Implementation

## Overview

This lab demonstrates how to design and implement VLANs in an enterprise environment. Instead of simply creating VLANs, the lab focuses on planning, documentation, security, and operational best practices.

## Objectives

- Create enterprise VLANs
- Assign switch ports
- Secure unused interfaces
- Configure PortFast and BPDU Guard
- Document interface assignments
- Verify VLAN operation

## VLAN Plan

| VLAN | Name |
|------|------|
| 10 | HR |
| 20 | SALES |
| 30 | IT |
| 99 | MANAGEMENT |
| 999 | BLACKHOLE |

## Skills Learned

- VLAN Design
- Access Port Configuration
- Interface Documentation
- Port Security Best Practices
- Broadcast Domain Segmentation
- Enterprise Switch Configuration

## Verification

- show vlan brief
- show interfaces status
- show running-config

## Lessons Learned

VLANs improve security, reduce broadcast traffic, and simplify network management. Proper planning, documentation, and securing unused ports are essential enterprise practices.

